{% extends 'layout.html.twig' %}

{% block content %}
    <div class="jumbotron">
        <div class="snow foreground"></div>
        <div class="snow foreground layered"></div>
        <div class="snow middleground"></div>
        <div class="snow middleground layered"></div>

        <div class="jumbotron-inner">
            <h1>Throw a Secret Santa with<br> your Slack team!</h1>

            <q><strong>Secret Santa</strong> is a Western Christmas tradition in which members of a group or
                community are <strong>randomly</strong> assigned a person to whom they anonymously <strong>give a gift</strong>.</q>

            <a class="action hvr-buzz" href="{{ path('run', { application: 'slack' }) }}">
                <i class="fa fa-slack"></i> Add to Slack now
            </a>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-titan-white">
        <div class="app-outer-container">
            <div class="">
                <div class="app-container">
                    <img class="upper-app" src="{{ asset('images/app-home.png') }}" alt="User selection interface">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="content how-block">
        <h2 class="content-head is-center">How does it works?</h2>

        <section class="step-feature">
            <div class="step-feature-image">
                <img src="{{ asset('images/step-slack.png') }}">
            </div>
            <div class="step-feature-text">
                <h3>1. Connect to Your Slack</h3>
                <p>Click on the "Add to Slack" button below then authorize the app to access your Slack team.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="step-feature reverse">
            <div class="step-feature-image">
                <img src="{{ asset('images/step-users.png') }}">
            </div>
            <div class="step-feature-text">
                <h3>2. Select Users</h3>
                <p>We show you all your Slack users (excluding the bots, because they don't do nice gifts). Just select which users will take part to your secret santa.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="step-feature">
            <div class="step-feature-image">
                <img src="{{ asset('images/step-inform.png') }}">
            </div>
            <div class="step-feature-text">
                <h3>3. Inform Users</h3>
                <p>After <a href="https://github.com/jolicode/slack-secret-santa/blob/master/src/Rudolph.php">Rudolph</a> shuffled the users, we throw at each participant a private message with his peer name and an optional admin message.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="step-feature reverse">
            <div class="step-feature-image">
                <img src="{{ asset('images/step-buy.png') }}">
            </div>
            <div class="step-feature-text">
                <h3>4. Buy a Gift</h3>
                <p>Everything is now setup. Just go buy a gift for your peer before your party. Merry Christmas!</p>
            </div>
        </section>
    </div>

    <div class="sample-message pure-g">
        <div class="sample-message-inner">
            <div class="pure-u-1 pure-u-md-1-1 pure-u-lg-2-5">
                <h2 class="content-head">Private message sent to users</h2>

                <p>
                    Each user will receive a private message to inform them of their peer name.
                    You can provide an optional message to inform your team about budget or deadline.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="is-center pure-u-1 pure-u-md-1-1 pure-u-lg-3-5">
                <img class="pure-img-responsive" alt="Sample message received by users" src="{{ asset('images/slack-sample.png') }}">
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="content why-block">
        <h2 class="content-head is-center">Why do I need this app?</h2>

        <p>
            At <a href="https://jolicode.com/">JoliCode</a>, we do a Secret Santa every year. Before this application,
            we had to ask someone from outside the company to be our "Secret Santa", running a script to dispatch users
            and sending emails to everyone.
        </p>

        <p>
            This time is gone! Because all our collaborators are on Slack, we can just select them from this interface
            and the application does all the work to shuffle users and to informe them of their peer name.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="content love-block pure-g">
        <div class="pure-u-1">
            <h2 class="content-head">Enjoy gifts, love and privacy</h2>
            <p>
                Secret Santa is about sharing and having a good time! This application does not persist anything on disk,
                does not use web analytics, does not need any registration, does not send spam, does not collect any kind
                of personal information and is integrally <a href="https://github.com/jolicode/slack-secret-santa/">open-source</a>.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
{% endblock content %}
